.TH "hw_cfg_broad_storm" 9 "hw_cfg_broad_storm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hw_cfg_broad_storm \- configure broadcast storm
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" hw_cfg_broad_storm
.BI "(struct ksz_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u8 percent "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
The hardware instance.
.IP "percent" 12
Broadcast storm threshold in percent of transmit rate.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine configures the broadcast storm threshold of the switch.
It is called by user functions.  The hardware should be acquired first.
